# Exclude project management artifacts from distribution
_bmad/
_bmad-output/
openspec/
docs/
test/
loadtest/
# Source trees that are replaced by their built artifacts in the dist:
#   app/      → compiled bytecode in precompiled/ (do_deploy runs `play precompile`
#                before `play dist`; runtime starts with -Dprecompiled=true,
#                which per Play 1.x's deployment.textile skips the compile pass).
#   frontend/ → built static SPA in public/spa/ (do_deploy runs `nuxi generate`
#                + copies .output/public to public/spa/ before `play dist`).
# An end-user dist install therefore needs only a JDK to run; no javac, no
# Node/pnpm, no source trees.
app/
frontend/
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
Dockerfile
docker-entrypoint.sh
Jenkinsfile
Jenkinsfile.renovate
.distignore
.dockerignore
.gitignore
# Developer-only tooling — git hooks, dev container config, AI assistant
# state, the Renovate bot's dependency-update config, and the Play fork
# version pin (consumed only at Docker build time, irrelevant at
# runtime) all belong to the source repo, not to a `play dist` tarball
# an end user unzips.
.githooks/
.devcontainer/
.claude/
renovate.json5
.play-version
# Build-time coverage artifacts (Jenkins only; not for the prod zip).
# bin/ + conf/jacoco-agent.properties ship in the source repo so the
# `%test.javaagent.path` line in conf/application.conf still resolves
# when someone runs `play auto-test` from a fresh clone, but the
# generated jacoco.exec / jacoco.xml should never ride into prod.
jacoco.exec
jacoco.xml
bin/
conf/jacoco-agent.properties
